## 📊 Results

The proposed Human Activity Recognition (HAR) system demonstrates strong performance in both accuracy and real-time inference on edge devices.

### 🔹 Model Performance
- Achieved high training and validation accuracy
- Successfully learned spatial features for activity classification
- Generalized well to unseen data

### 🔹 Evaluation Metrics
- Confusion Matrix used to analyze classification performance
- ROC Curve shows strong class separation capability
- Precision–Recall analysis indicates reliable predictions across activities

### 🔹 Real-Time Performance
- Achieves low latency during live video processing
- Smooth frame-by-frame prediction using optimized CNN model
- Stable output using prediction smoothing technique

### 🔹 Impact of Quantization
- Reduced model size by ~75%
- Faster inference using INT8 operations
- Lower memory consumption
- Maintains acceptable accuracy after optimization

### 🔹 System Output
- Real-time activity prediction displayed on video feed
- Shows activity label and confidence score
- Works efficiently on Raspberry Pi (edge device)

### 🔹 Sample Predictions
- Sitting → High confidence
- Running → Accurately detected
- Eating / Texting → Correct classification in most cases

